<br>
Obviously everyone agrees that practice makes perfect, its the only way your gonna get better at drawing face it....<br>
Also, in my case, drawing to me is like riding a bike, there was a moment in my life, about a year that i stopped drawing, then one day i started drawing, and i couldn't believe it, i still had it.  And from there on i haven't stopped drawing.... The End.<br>
<br>
Id like to bring to attention what Nemethyst said.<br>
Its important that you don't push yourself too much if your NOT having fun.  Beacuse if your not having fun, 8 out of 10 times your probably not gonna finish what your started, then you'll probably get upset and never want to draw again, and your interest level will decline, and who wants to draw with no interest!  Believe me, I know!  <br>
If your frustrated with your drawing, put it down relax and take a breather, think about what you want to accomplish and sit on it.  Come back to it later, and if your still having some probs, go on the net and try looking for the pose your trying to draw, if ya can't find an exact pose, you should be able to find one that has the legs in the position your trying to draw, or the torso, etc.....<br>
<br>
I'd also suggest copying your favorite anime characters, that always helps to get an idea of how other artists draw and bring about sum ideas, but be forwarn,<br>
copying is not gonna make you draw like the pros, its just a step to help you with your skills.  One more thing, find a pose and draw it over and over until it start to looks good, once your happy with what you have go to the next pose, and the next pose and the next.... see!!!!<br>
<br>
Hope this helps, and stay with it, it'll come along. It took me at least a couple of months to get my drawings the way i wanted them, then years to perfect, and im still climbing the pyramid if you know what i mean.<br>
<br>
Remember, have fun, relax, and most important of all Practice!!!!<br>
<br>
Dammit, i wish i had a scanner!  I could show you what my  first drawings looked like about 5 yrs ago compared to todays.<br>
<br>
<br>
-chaos<br>
